post.summary: Send delivery address info to seller
post.description:
Selects a delivery address for an auction you've won and sends that
  information, along with an optional phone number and message, to the seller.
  Do not use this API if the buyer is planning to pay with Pay Now, since the
  Pay Now process already includes this step. An address can only be sent once;
  the buyer must contact the seller directly if there was a mistake.

parameters.name: file_format
parameters.description: The format of the response.

200.description: <SendDeliveryAddressResponse> Indicates whether or not the operation succeeded.

post.summary: Adds an image to the authenticated user's list of branding images
post.description: Adds an image to the authenticated user's list of branding images. These photos can be used when listing a classified. Branding images are only supported for Job listings.

parameters.name: file_format
parameters.description: The format of the response.

200.description:
<UploadBrandingResponse> Information about the uploaded branding


 Success 
 Boolean 

Indicates whether the operation was successful.



 Description 
 String or null 

The description of the error, if the operation failed.



 BrandingImageDetails 
 <BrandingImageDetails> or null 

The uploaded image information









 Links 
 Collection of <Link> or null 

Links to related operations




 Example JSON Request  
{
  "FileName": "ABC",
  "BrandingImageType": 0,
  "ImageData": "ABC"
}


 Example JSON Response  
{
  "Success": false,
  "Description": "ABC",
  "BrandingImageDetails": {
  },
  "Links": [
    {
      "Href": "ABC",
      "Rel": "ABC",
      "Prompt": "ABC",
      "Method": "ABC"
    },
    {
      "Href": "ABC",
      "Rel": "ABC",
      "Prompt": "ABC",
      "Method": "ABC"
    }
  ]
}

get.summary: Retrieve detailed information about a single category by mcat path
get.description:
Retrieves detailed information about a single category. This includes
          applicable attributes, a legal notice (for categories that have one),
          available listing durations, listing fees and information about
          whether classifieds and/or auctions are allowed to be sold within the
          category.

parameters.name: file_format
parameters.description: The format of the response.

parameters.name: mcat_path
parameters.description:
The string path of the category. If this parameter is empty, it
                returns a fictional category named "Root".

200.description: <CategoryDetails>

get.summary: Retrieve detailed information about a single category
get.description: Retrieves detailed information about a single category. This includes applicable attributes, a legal notice (for categories that have one), available listing durations, listing fees and information about whether classifieds and/or auctions are allowed to be sold within the category.

parameters.name: category
parameters.description: The ID of the category to retrieve information on.

parameters.name: file_format
parameters.description: The format of the response.

parameters.name: as_at
parameters.description: The date for which the information applies. Intended for use when editing since fees when editing are based on the listing start date, not the current date. If supplied, the date must be in the past. Currently only affects fee information.

parameters.name: catalogue
parameters.description: Indicates whether you intend to list a DVD or Blu-ray listing via the catalogue. Only applies to DVD and Blu-ray categories.

200.description: <CategoryDetails>

get.description: Returns a list of DVD catalogue ID numbers. You can use this list to validate the catalogue ID before listing a DVD. These ID numbers don't change very often so you should cache them and only periodically refresh them.

parameters.name: file_format

200.description: Collection of <DvdValidation> A list containing the IDs of all DVD titles.

get.summary: Retrieve general categories by mcat path
get.description: Retrieves all or part of the Trade Me category tree.

parameters.name: file_format
parameters.description: The format of the response.

parameters.name: depth
parameters.description: The depth of the category tree to return. 0 = a single category. 1 = the specified category plus any subcategories. The default is to return all subcategories.

parameters.name: mcat_path
parameters.description: The string path of the category. If this parameter is empty, it returns a fictional category named "Root" with all the top categories included as subcategories.

parameters.name: region
parameters.description: The ID of the region used to filter listing counts. Only applicable if with_counts is true.

parameters.name: with_counts
parameters.description: Indicates whether to include the number of listings in each category. Defaults to false.

200.description: <Category> A category tree.

parameters.name: with_counts

get.summary: Retrieve Property, Jobs and Services districts
get.description: Returns the districts and suburbs within the region with the given ID. These values are used in Trade Me Property, Trade Me Jobs and Services.

parameters.name: regionId
parameters.description: The region ID to get districts and suburbs for.

parameters.name: file_format
parameters.description: The format of the response.

parameters.name: listing_type
parameters.description: The type of listing to include in the count property, if with_counts is true. Valid values are "HOUSES_TO_BUY", "HOUSES_TO_RENT", "COMMERCIAL_FOR_SALE", "COMMERCIAL_FOR_LEASE", "FLATMATES_WANTED", "RURAL", "RETIREMENT_VILLAGES" and "LIFESTYLE". Defaults to "HOUSES_TO_BUY".

parameters.name: with_counts
parameters.description: Indicates whether to include the listing count for each district. Defaults to false.

200.description: Collection of <Locality>

This will send an email to the buyer and will make the payment instructions available on the Trade Me website, mobile apps and third-party tools. Payment instructions can only be sent once, and cannot be sent at all if the buyer has already paid via Pay Now. You can check if payment instructions have been sent using the InvoiceId field (in the sold items API) or the PaymentInstructions field (in the listing details API). You can check if the buyer has paid using Pay Now using the IsPayNowPurchase field (in the sold items API) or the HasPaidByCreditCard field (in the listing details API).

Bold.description:
The price of the bold title promotion. Listings with this
                      promotion have a bold title in search results. If the
                      property is not present, then this promotion is not
                      available.

Bundle.description:
The price of having the feature, bold and gallery
                      promotions. If the property is not present, then this
                      promotion is not available. Note that some categories do
                      not allow certain promotions - in this case only the
                      supported promotions are included in the price.

EndDate.description:
The price of the scheduled end time promotion. If the
                      property is not present, then this promotion is not
                      available.

Feature.description:
The price of the feature promotion. Listings with this
                      promotion are shown higher in search results. If the
                      property is not present, then this promotion is not
                      available.

Gallery.description:
The price of the gallery promotion. Listings with this
                      promotion show photos in search results. If the property
                      is not present, then this promotion is not available.

GalleryPlus.description:
The price of the gallery plus promotion. Listings with
                      this promotion get the gallery promotion, plus the next
                      two relists also get the gallery promotion if the item
                      doesn't sell. If the property is not present, then this
                      promotion is not available.

Highlight.description:
The price of the highlight promotion. Listings with this
                      promotion have a bright yellow border. If the property is
                      not present, then this promotion is not available.

Homepage.description:
The price of featuring the listing on the homepage. If the
                      property is not present, then this promotion is not
                      available.

Listing.description:
The base price of listing an item. Applies to classifieds
                      and auctions in some categories. Note that in some
                      categories the fee for listing a classified depends on the
                      asking price (or the rateable value/rent per week for
                      properties) - for these categories this property will
                      contain the price at the lowest tier. If this property is
                      not present, then there is no listing fee for this
                      category. For Motors the field is only applicable to
                      Auctions

MultiPhoto.description:
The price for additional photos. If the property is not
                      present, then this promotion is not available.

Reserve.description:
The price for having a reserve. If the property is not
                      present, then this promotion is not available.

Subtitle.description:
The cost of the subtitle promotion. Listings with this
                      promotion have a subtitle in search results and listing
                      pages. If the property is not present, then this promotion
                      is not available.

TenDays.description:
The price to extend the listing to a duration of 10 days.
                      If the property is not present, then this promotion is not
                      available.

Withdrawal.description:
The minimum withdrawal fee for a listing. For some
                      categories, including Motors, the withdrawal fee is
                      calculated based on the sale price of the item at the time
                      of the withdrawal. Withdrawing the item in the first hour
                      is fee.Retrieve fees for withdrawing a listingendpoint is used to calculate the correct value.

SuperFeature.description:
The price for the super feature promotion. Listings with
                      the super feature promotion are listed on the landing page
                      for certain verticals, such as Trade Me Motors. This price
                      is irrelevant for general marketplace listings. This is
                      the price for super feature only - it does not include the
                      feature combo extras. It is only available when adding the
                      super feature promotion to a listing which had it already,
                      but where the super feature period has expired. If the
                      property is not present, then this promotion is not
                      available.

SuperFeatureBundle.description:
The price for the super feature promotion. Listings with
                      the super feature promotion are listed on the landing page
                      for categories in general marketplace and verticals, such
                      as Trade Me Motors. This price includes feature, bold,
                      highlight and gallery, where applicable. If the property
                      is not present, then this promotion is not available.

HighVolume.description:
The price for listing more than a set number of listings
                      concurrently. The maximum number of listings you can run
                      without incurring a fee starts at 50, but increases based
                      on the number of items you have sold. See ourhelp pagefor more information. This fee does not apply to
                      classifieds. This fee is the same for all categories (i.e.
                      it is not category-specific).

ListingFeeTiers.description:
If the listing fee is dependent on the asking price, then
                      this field will contain a list of pricing tiers. Only
                      applies to categories where a tiered listing fee has been
                      applied.

MinimumTierPrice.description:
The minimum price (may be the sale price, asking
                            price, rateable value or rent per week, depending on
                            the category and the type of fee) for this tier. The
                            maximum price for this tier is defined by the
                            minimum price for the next tier (if this is the last
                            tier, then the maximum price is unlimited).

FixedFee.description:
The fixed fee that applies to listings within this
                            tier. If the PercentageFee property is also present,
                            then this fee applies in addition to that one.

PercentageFee.description:
The fee that applies to listings within this tier,
                            as a percentage of the price increase over the
                            minimum tier price. For example, if this fee applies
                            to a sale price of $250, the MinimumTierPrice is
                            $200, and the PercentageFee is 4.9, then this fee is
                            4.9% of the $50 which amounts to $2.45. If the
                            FixedFee property is present, then this fee applies
                            in addition to that one.

MinimumSuccessFee.description:
The minimum success fee. Success fees only apply to
                      auctions. If the property is not present, then the minimum
                      success fee is zero.

MaximumSuccessFee.description:
The maximum success fee. Success fees only apply to
                      auctions. If the property is not present, then success
                      fees do not apply to this category.

SuccessFeeTiers.description:
A list of success fee tiers. Only applies to auctions. If
                      the property is not present, then success fees do not
                      apply to this category.

Branding.description:
The price of the branding promotion. Listings with this
                      promotion can have logo and/or banner. If the property is
                      not present, then this promotion is not available.

SecondCategory.description:
The price of the second category promotion. Listings with
                      this promotion will also appear in the second category
                      selected.

Discounts.description:
Additional information regarding member specific discounts
                      for this category. The discount values are already applied
                      to the Fees.

Type.description: Fee discount type.

Bold.description: The price of the bold title promotion. Listings with this promotion have a bold title in search results. If the property is not present, then this promotion is not available.

Bundle.description: The price of having the feature, bold and gallery promotions. If the property is not present, then this promotion is not available. Note that some categories do not allow certain promotions - in this case only the supported promotions are included in the price.

EndDate.description: The price of the scheduled end time promotion. If the property is not present, then this promotion is not available.

Feature.description: The price of the feature promotion. Listings with this promotion are shown higher in search results. If the property is not present, then this promotion is not available.

Gallery.description: The price of the gallery promotion. Listings with this promotion show photos in search results. If the property is not present, then this promotion is not available.

GalleryPlus.description: The price of the gallery plus promotion. Listings with this promotion get the gallery promotion, plus the next two relists also get the gallery promotion if the item doesn't sell. If the property is not present, then this promotion is not available.

Highlight.description: The price of the highlight promotion. Listings with this promotion have a bright yellow border. If the property is not present, then this promotion is not available.

Homepage.description: The price of featuring the listing on the homepage. If the property is not present, then this promotion is not available.

Listing.description: The base price of listing an item. Applies to classifieds and auctions in some categories. Note that in some categories the fee for listing a classified depends on the asking price (or the rateable value/rent per week for properties) - for these categories this property will contain the price at the lowest tier. If this property is not present, then there is no listing fee for this category. For Motors the field is only applicable to Auctions

MultiPhoto.description: The price for additional photos. If the property is not present, then this promotion is not available.

Reserve.description: The price for having a reserve. If the property is not present, then this promotion is not available.

Subtitle.description: The cost of the subtitle promotion. Listings with this promotion have a subtitle in search results and listing pages. If the property is not present, then this promotion is not available.

TenDays.description: The price to extend the listing to a duration of 10 days. If the property is not present, then this promotion is not available.

Withdrawal.description: The minimum withdrawal fee for a listing. For some categories, including Motors, the withdrawal fee is calculated based on the sale price of the item at the time of the withdrawal. Withdrawing the item in the first hour is fee.Retrieve fees for withdrawing a listingendpoint is used to calculate the correct value.

SuperFeature.description: The price for the super feature promotion. Listings with the super feature promotion are listed on the landing page for certain verticals, such as Trade Me Motors. This price is irrelevant for general marketplace listings. This is the price for super feature only - it does not include the feature combo extras. It is only available when adding the super feature promotion to a listing which had it already, but where the super feature period has expired. If the property is not present, then this promotion is not available.

SuperFeatureBundle.description: The price for the super feature promotion. Listings with the super feature promotion are listed on the landing page for categories in general marketplace and verticals, such as Trade Me Motors. This price includes feature, bold, highlight and gallery, where applicable. If the property is not present, then this promotion is not available.

HighVolume.description: The price for listing more than a set number of listings concurrently. The maximum number of listings you can run without incurring a fee starts at 50, but increases based on the number of items you have sold. See ourhelp pagefor more information. This fee does not apply to classifieds. This fee is the same for all categories (i.e. it is not category-specific).

ListingFeeTiers.description: If the listing fee is dependent on the asking price, then this field will contain a list of pricing tiers. Only applies to categories where a tiered listing fee has been applied.

MinimumTierPrice.description: The minimum price (may be the sale price, asking price, rateable value or rent per week, depending on the category and the type of fee) for this tier. The maximum price for this tier is defined by the minimum price for the next tier (if this is the last tier, then the maximum price is unlimited).

FixedFee.description: The fixed fee that applies to listings within this tier. If the PercentageFee property is also present, then this fee applies in addition to that one.

PercentageFee.description: The fee that applies to listings within this tier, as a percentage of the price increase over the minimum tier price. For example, if this fee applies to a sale price of $250, the MinimumTierPrice is $200, and the PercentageFee is 4.9, then this fee is 4.9% of the $50 which amounts to $2.45. If the FixedFee property is present, then this fee applies in addition to that one.

MinimumSuccessFee.description: The minimum success fee. Success fees only apply to auctions. If the property is not present, then the minimum success fee is zero.

MaximumSuccessFee.description: The maximum success fee. Success fees only apply to auctions. If the property is not present, then success fees do not apply to this category.

SuccessFeeTiers.description: A list of success fee tiers. Only applies to auctions. If the property is not present, then success fees do not apply to this category.

Branding.description: The price of the branding promotion. Listings with this promotion can have logo and/or banner. If the property is not present, then this promotion is not available.

SecondCategory.description: The price of the second category promotion. Listings with this promotion will also appear in the second category selected.

Discounts.description: Additional information regarding member specific discounts for this category. The discount values are already applied to the Fees.

Category.description: The ID of the category to list the item in. For example, specify "6853" to list an oil heater. This field also accepts the MCAT category format (e.g. "0004-0370-0560-6853-"). Ignored when listing from the DVD/Blu-ray catalogue.

Title.description: The title of the listing. Maximum of 80 characters for Marketplace categories, 50 for the other businesses. Mandatory for most categories. In some categories (e.g. used cars, motorbikes, flatmates wanted) the title is based on one or more attributes. In these categories the title is optional, and is ignored if it is supplied. Not required when listing from the DVD/Blu-ray catalogue.

Subtitle.description: The subtitle of the listing. Optional. Maximum of 50 characters.

Description.description: A short description of the promotion.

StartPrice.description: The start price of the listing. Mandatory for auctions. Must be a minimum of 50c and must be less than or equal to the ReservePrice. For most classifieds this value is optional: if specified it is the value that is displayed as the ‘Asking price’. A notable exception to this rule are business for sale classifieds. Not used for property listings (subcategories of category 350); use the PropertyPricePrice attribute instead.

ReservePrice.description: The reserve price of the listing. Optional. If supplied, it must be a minimum of 50c and it must be greater than or equal to the StartPrice. Only applicable to auctions, ignored for classifieds.

BuyNowPrice.description: The Buy Now price of the listing. Optional. Must be a minimum of 50c, must be greater than or equal to the StartPrice. For Buy Now Only auctions quantity and shipping information must be specified. See Quantity and IsFlatShippingCharge. Only applicable to auctions, ignored for classifieds.

Duration.description: The duration of the listing. Mandatory. Must be one of the durations available as per the category details API. Can be a fixed duration or a specified end time.

EndDateTime.description: The date and time the listing should close. Ignored unless Duration is set to EndDate.

Pickup.description: Indicates whether the buyer can (or is required to) pick-up the item. For auctions any value other than Demand implies that at least one shipping option must be provided. For classifieds this value is ignored.
x-enum-descriptions: The listing allows pick up, but does not require it.
The buyer can pickup if they so choose.
The buyer must pickup the item.
The buyer cannot pickup the item (delivery only).

PickupSuburbId.description: If the buyer can (or is required to) pick-up the item then this field can be used to specify the pick-up suburb id. It uses the three-tier region/district/suburb system. Optional. Only applicable to auctions, ignored for classifieds.

IsBrandNew.description: Indicates whether the listing is for a brand new item. Optional, defaults to false. Only applicable to auctions, ignored for classifieds.

AuthenticatedMembersOnly.description: Determines if only authenticated members can bid on the listing. Only applicable to auctions, ignored for classifieds.

IsClassified.description: Determines if this listing is a classified or an auction. Optional, defaults to false. Some categories support auctions, some support classifieds and some accept both types. Use the category details API to check which types a category supports.

OpenHomes.description: A list of upcoming open home times. Currently only applies to residential for sale (category 3399) and lifestyle (category 9120) listings.

Start.description: The date and time the open home is open for viewing. The date must be in the future and it must be less than 56 days from the current date. Specify dates in the UTC time zone.

End.description: The date and time the open home is no longer open for viewing. Must be the same day as Start.

SendPaymentInstructions.description: Determines if only the payment instructions are sent at the end of the listing Specifies if automatic payment instructions email will be sent to the winner of the auction. Optional, defaults to false.

OtherPaymentMethod.description: If the list of payment methods includes Other then this field can be used to specify the name of the payment method. Optional. Only applicable to auctions that have the Other payment method.

IsOrNearOffer.description: Specifies if ‘ONO’ should be displayed with price on listing. Optional. Applicable only to classified listings.

IsPriceOnApplication.description: Specifies that the price should be displayed as "Price on Application". Optional. Applicable only to businesses for sale listings (subcategories of category 36).

IsBold.description: Applies the bold promotion onto the listing. Only permitted in categories that support bold. Whether or not it’s available in a category can be confirmed using the Fees API endpoint. Note that a discount may be applicable if all the feature combo promotions are specified (feature, bold, highlight and gallery). Also note that promotions cannot be removed from a listing.

IsFeatured.description: Applies the feature promotion onto the listing. Only permitted in categories that support this promotion. Whether or not it’s available in a category can be confirmed using the Fees API endpoint. Note that a discount may be applicable if all the feature combo promotions are specified (feature, bold, highlight and gallery). Also note that promotions cannot be removed from a listing.

HasGallery.description: Applies the gallery promotion onto the listing. Only permitted in categories that support this promotion. Whether or not it’s available in a category can be confirmed using the Fees API endpoint. Note that a discount may be applicable if all the feature combo promotions are specified (feature, bold, highlight and gallery). Also note that promotions cannot be removed from a listing.

HasGalleryPlus.description: Applies the gallery plus promotion onto the listing. Only permitted in categories that support this promotion. Whether or not it’s available in a category can be confirmed using the Fees API endpoint. This promotion cannot be applied to a listing that already has the gallery promotion. Note that promotions cannot be removed from a listing.

Quantity.description: This is the quantity of items that are available for sale. Can be between 1 and 1000. Note that when editing, the value must be less than or equal to 1000 - (quantity sold). The quantity sold for a listing can be calculated by adding up all the QuantitySold values from the listing details response.

IsFlatShippingCharge.description: For Buy Now Only auctions this specifies if the shipping is one rate for multiple quantities. If false is specified the winning bidder will be charged the shipping rate multiplied by the quantity of items purchased. If true is specified one flat shipping rate is charged. Only applicable for auctions, ignored for classifieds.

HasAgreedWithLegalNotice.description: Specifies if the user has read and agreed with the legal notice relevant to the category the listing is being created in. The category details API can be used to retrieve the legal notice for a specific category (only applies to certain categories, such as the category 6327 - Carbon Credits).

HomePhoneNumber.description: Home phone number to be displayed on listing. Optional. Only applicable in categories where the user has paid a listing fee. Must be 9 digits long and use a valid area code. Can be specified but will only be displayed when category permits.

MobilePhoneNumber.description: Mobile phone number to be displayed on listing. Optional. Only applicable in categories where the user has paid a listing fee. Must be 8 or 9 digits long. Can be specified but will only be displayed when category permits.

IsHighlighted.description: Applies the “highlight” promotion onto the listing. Only permitted in categories that support this promotion. Whether or not it’s available in a category can be confirmed using the Fees API endpoint. Note that a discount may be applicable if all the feature combo promotions are specified (feature, bold, highlight and gallery). Also note that promotions cannot be removed from a listing.

HasSuperFeature.description: Applies the “super feature” promotion onto the listing. Only permitted in categories that support this promotion. Whether or not it’s available in a category can be confirmed using the Fees API endpoint. Note that when creating a new listing with the super feature promotion, the feature, bold, highlight and gallery promotions will automatically be applied. Also note that promotions cannot be removed from a listing.

PhotoIds.description: Photo IDs for images that have already been uploaded that you want to display on the listing. For all general items categories all photos are free (up to 20 max). Check the  category details API for exact details. Note that photos may be deleted if they are unused for too long. It is up to you to ensure that your photo IDs are valid. See our  photo retention policy for more information.

ShippingOptions.description: The shipping options to be displayed on the listing. Can contain up to ten shipping options. Mandatory for auctions, ignored for classifieds.

Type.description: The type of delivery.

Indicates the item can be shipped for free within New Zealand. When listing an item, this option cannot be used in combination with other shipping options.
Custom shipping option. Allows the seller to specify the price and description. Multiple custom shipping options are allowed (up to ten).
Trademe shipping option. Allows the seller to calculate the quotes from couriers, all calculated quotes will be saved in custom shipping options.

Price.description: The Buy Now price of the variant. Must be a minimum of 50c.

Method.description: The name of the delivery method (e.g. "NZ Courier", "Rural Delivery"). Only applicable if ShippingType is Custom.

ShippingId.description: The ID of the shipping option (used when bidding or for Buy Now). Not required when listing an item.

PaymentMethods.description: The acceptable payment methods to be displayed on the listing. Mandatory for auctions, ignored for classifieds.

Attributes.description: A collection of dynamic attributes that relate to this variant specifically. These can be any number of name-value pairs. Some well-known attribute names will also help users find your listings: Google Shopping Feed We include attributes that are named and correctly formatted in a feed that goes to Google Shopping. These are Brand, GTIN and Manufacturer Code so include this data if you have it.

Unit.description: The selected unit. Only applicable to attributes that have at least one associated unit. This field is optional, but if supplied, will be saved along with the value. The list of valid units can be retrieved from the category details API.

IsClearance.description: This indicates that the listing is a clearance item. Clearance listings include listings with was/now pricing and general clearance stock.

ExternalReferenceId.description: Allows the API client to associate an identifier (or any short string) against the listing. This value can be searched on but is otherwise only accessible via the API. Not used by Trade Me. Optional. Max 50 characters.

Contacts.description: A list of contact details. Optional. Currently only applicable for property categories and property agents that have billing methods covering the type of category. For example to add contact details in the residential for rent category the agent must have residential for rent billing enabled.

FullName.description: The full name of the contact person or agent. Mandatory.

PhoneNumber.description: The phone number of the contact. Can be either a mobile or landline number. Optional.

AlternatePhoneNumber.description: The phone number of the contact. Can be either a mobile or landline number. This is the primary contact number on the Trade Me Apps. Optional.

EMail.description: The email address of the contact to be used for email enquiries. Optional.

BrandingImageId.description: The ID of the branding image to display an agent photo on this listing. See the  upload branding image API. Optional.

AgencyName.description: The agency name for the contact

VariantDefinition.description: When specified, turns the listing request into a multi-variant listing that creates several child listings. The variants definition is used to describe the variant options that are available and the combinations of variants that make up the multi-variant listing.

Values.description: The choices available for this option set, e.g. "red", "blue". The sequence in which values are supplied is reflected in the sequence of user-interface elements on listings.

Photos.description: A collection of photo URLs for the listing. Ignored when creating or editing a listing.

Thumbnail.description: The URL for the thumbnail sized photo (always 85x64, with white borders).

List.description: The URL for the list view sized photo (scaled down to fit 160x120).

Medium.description: The URL for the medium sized photo (scaled down to fit 175x175).

Gallery.description: The URL for the gallery sized photo (scaled down to fit 233x176).

Large.description: The URL for the large sized photo (scaled down to fit 352x264).

FullSize.description: The URL for the full sized photo (scaled down to fit 670x502).

PlusSize.description: The URL for the plus sized photo (scaled down to fit).

Options.description: The combination of variant options that this variant represents.

ListingId.description: The ID of the listing to edit.

ProductSpecification.description: The specifications of the product if the listing relates to a product. If this is a multi-variant product, specify these in the Variants section.

GTIN.description: The GTIN of the product e.g. 027242896505

Brand.description: The brand name of the product e.g. Sony

ManufacturerCode.description: The product code used by the manufacturer e.g. KDL32W600D

SecondCategory.description: The ID of the second category to list the item in. For example, specify "6853" to list an oil heater. This field also accepts the MCAT category format (e.g. "0004-0370-0560-6853-"). Not all categories can be used as a second category and not all primary categories can be paired with a second category.

PremiumPackageCode.description: The code of the premium package to apply to the listing. This will be null if a package is not applied to the listing or a package was previously applied but has since completed.

ListingExtrasLedger.description: A collection of extras that have been applied to the listing. This is an output field. We will provide Id, Name, Variant, StartDate, & EndDate. Any changes to this collection is ignored when creating or editing a listing.

HasGoodFor2Relists.description: Indicates if Good For 2 Relists is included with the premium package.

IsCounterOffersAllowed.description: Indicates if Make an Offer is enabled or not. true is enabled, false is disabled and null means it hasn't set yet.

MaximumOffers.description: The maximum number of Buyer offers the listing accepts if the listing has Counter Offers enabled.

ShippingTemplateId.description: The identifier of the shipping template containing the shipping options. For the shipping template to be successfully applied to the listing, there are some requirements to be met with the api request: The listing must be a Buy Now Only listing: Must have: - A quantity > 0 - A buy now price - Shipping field = 0 (or the field not supplied) Must not have: - A reserve price - A starting price - Any custom shipping options supplied - Pickup only The primary and/or secondary category supplied must be Marketplace categories. When the above requirements are not met when specifying a ShippingTemplateId, then the listing request will fail.Identifying marketplace categories You can identify these categories by using the following endpoint:Category Details When AreaOfBusiness = 1 (marketplace category)

Files.description: A list of files on the listing

RequiredMinimumReserve.description: The required minimum value for the Reserve field. This property will be returned when a listing has bids on it but has not yet met reserve. This field should not be set by consumers.

HasBeenExtended.description: Specifically exposed to be used by motor sell app, not public api

StartDate.description: The start date of the listing to edit. This field should not be set by consumers. Ignored on POST requests.

TotalCount.description: The total number of results in the collection. Can be larger than the number of returned results.

Page.description: The index of the current page of results (starts at 1).

PageSize.description: The number of results in the current page.

List.description: A list of the results in the current page.

ListingId.description: The ID of the listing this question belongs to.

CommentDate.description: The date and time the question was asked.

Answer.description: The answer given to the question by the owner of the listing.

AnswerDate.description: The date the question was answered.

IsSellerComment.description: Indicates whether this is a comment from the seller rather than a question.

AskingMember.description: The member details for the member asking the question.

MemberId.description: The ID of the member. This may be 0, if we determine it is necessary to protect the member's privacy.

Nickname.description: The nickname of the member. Some characters may be changed, if we determine it is necessary to protect the member's privacy.

DateAddressVerified.description: The date the member was address verified.

UniqueNegative.description: The number of distinct members who have placed negative feedback against this member.

UniquePositive.description: The number of distinct members who have placed positive feedback against this member.

FeedbackCount.description: The member's total feedback (UniquePositive minus UniqueNegative).

IsAddressVerified.description: Indicates whether the member has been address verified.

IsDealer.description: Indicates whether the member is a car dealer.

IsAuthenticated.description: Indicates whether the member is authenticated.

Photo.description: The profile photo URL of the member

TotalCount.description: The total number of results in the collection. Can be larger than the number of returned results.

Page.description: The index of the current page of results (starts at 1).

StartDate.description: The date the listing was created.

EndDate.description: The date the listing will end.

HasHomePageFeature.description: Is this a homepage feature listing?

AsAt.description: The date and time the response was generated on the server.

PictureHref.description: The URL of the primary photo for the listing (if the listing has a photo). By default you'll get a thumbnail-sized photo, but you can control the size of the photo using the photo_size parameter.

HasPayNow.description: Indicates whether the item has Pay Now.

IsNew.description: Indicates whether the item is marked as new.

RegionId.description:
The ID of the region where this item is located. In the general search, listing details and watchlist APIs this is the ID of the seller's region (using the two-tier region/suburb system), which means it might be inconsistent with the region name. In the property search API this is the ID of the property region, using the three-tier region/district/suburb system.

                                This field cannot cope with the two main geographical classification systems.  Except for the property search API, it should not be used.

SuburbId.description: The ID of the suburb where this item is located. Only populated by the property search API, which means it uses the three-tier region/district/suburb system.

PickupLocality.description: The pick-up location details if pick-up is allowed and has been specified.

District.description: The pickup district.

BidCount.description: The number of bids on the item.

IsReserveMet.description: Indicates whether the item's reserve has been met.

HasReserve.description: Indicates whether the item has a reserve.

HasBuyNow.description: Indicates whether the item has Buy Now.

NoteDate.description: The date of the note on an item.

ReserveState.description: The flag to display on an item.

Attributes.description: The attributes for the item that are intended to be displayed on the UI.

Value.description: The string value of the attribute. When listing, the valid values for the attribute can be determined using the "Retrieve attributes for a category" API. Use "false" or "true" for boolean attributes. Required when selling or editing.

IsClassified.description: Indicates whether the item is a classified.

OpenHomes.description: A collection of open home times for this listing. Only applies to open home listings.

Start.description: The date and time the open home is open for viewing. The date must be in the future and it must be less than 56 days from the current date. Specify dates in the UTC time zone.

End.description: The date and time the open home is no longer open for viewing. Must be the same day as Start.

IsBuyNowOnly.description: Indicates whether or not this is a Buy Now Only listing.

RemainingGalleryPlusRelists.description: The number of times the item can be relisted and get the gallery promotion for free. This value is only present if you are the seller and the listing had the gallery promotion applied due to the gallery plus promotion. Note that for this field, a value of zero is not the same as if the field is missing (a value of zero means gallery plus is in effect whereas if the field is missing it means that you are not the seller or gallery plus is not in effect).

IsOnWatchList.description: Indicates whether the item is on the authenticated member's watchlist.

GeographicLocation.description: The geographic location (latitude and longitude) of a property.

Attributes.description: The attributes for the item that are intended to be displayed on the UI.

Name.description: A name which uniquely identifies the attribute. Required when selling or editing.

DisplayName.description: The name of the attribute, in a form suitable for displaying to users. Not required when selling or editing.

Value.description: The string value of the attribute. When listing, the valid values for the attribute can be determined using the "Retrieve attributes for a category" API. Use "false" or "true" for boolean attributes. Required when selling or editing.

IsClassified.description: Indicates whether the item is a classified.

ReservePrice.description: The reserve price for the auction. This is available in the sold/unsold items APIs and, if you are the seller, the listing details API.

IsBuyNowOnly.description: Indicates whether or not this is a Buy Now Only listing.

Quantity.description: The total quantity available of the item. Only applicable for Buy Now Only listings. When retrieving won items this value represents the number sold, not the total quantity. When retrieving sold items, this value is not present (use QuantitySold instead). When retrieving listing details, this value is only present if you are the seller.

RemainingGalleryPlusRelists.description: The number of times the item can be relisted and get the gallery promotion for free. This value is only present if you are the seller and the listing had the gallery promotion applied due to the gallery plus promotion. Note that for this field, a value of zero is not the same as if the field is missing (a value of zero means gallery plus is in effect whereas if the field is missing it means that you are not the seller or gallery plus is not in effect).

PriceDisplay.description: The price, in a format suitable for displaying to the user. Some categories may have special pricing rules, e.g. properties may have "Price by negotiation".

ExternalReferenceId.description: The external reference ID, if one exists. Only available to the seller of a listing.

SKU.description: SKU or Stock Keeping Unit. Used to uniquely identify an auction's product line.

IsClearance.description: This indicates that the listing is a clearance item. Clearance listings include listings with was/now pricing and general clearance stock.

WasPrice.description: The usual price that a product is sold at, or the price before it was marked down. This is always more than the Buy Now price for Auctions, or more than the asking price for Classifieds.This field will only be populated if IsClearance is true.

PercentageOff.description: The percentage that a product has been discounted. This has been rounded for display purposes. This field will only be populated if IsClearance is true.

Branding.description: A list of branding images associated with this listing.

LargeSquareLogo.description: A large square branding image with dimensions of 480x480.

Fee.description: The fee associated with the transaction. This value is omitted if there is no associated fee. This value is never negative.

SettlementId.description: An ID that can be used to get the breakdown of a settlement. Only populated if the payment type is PaymentToMemberBankAccount (or FailedPaymentToMemberBankAccount).

LedgerId.description: The unique identifier for this ledger item.

TotalNzGst.description: The total NZ GST collected on this sale by Trade Me to be forwarded to IRD

TotalCount.description: The total number of results in the collection. Can be larger than the number of returned results.

Page.description: The index of the current page of results (starts at 1).

PageSize.description: The number of results in the current page.

Template.description: The payment instructions template. This should not include a salutation ("Hi John"). If payment instructions haven't been set up then this will be null.

CopySeller.description: Indicates whether the seller's preference is to CC payment instructions emails. The default is false.

WatchListCount.description: The number of items on the watchlist.

SellingCount.description: The number of items being sold.

MemberId.description: The ID of the member.

Nickname.description: The member's nickname.

DateJoined.description: The date the member registered for an account on Trade Me.

DateAddressVerified.description: The date and time the member became address verified, if they are address verified.

IsAddressVerified.description: Indicates whether the member is address verified. This means the member entered a code that was delivered via the postal system to the member's street address. Note that currently, members retain their address verified status if they move, so having this status doesn't necessarily mean that the member's current address is valid.

Balance.description: The member's Trade Me account balance.

PayNowBalance.description: The member's Pay Now account balance.

FixedPriceOffers.description: The number of fixed price offers for the member.

Email.description: The email address for the member.

IsMembershipAddress.description: Indicates whether this address is a membership address. This type of address is comprised of address details that are supplied when registering an account. Do not supply this value when adding or updating a delivery address.

IsBusiness.description: Indicates whether the member has registered as a business.

BusinessName.description: The member's business name (business memberships only).

BillingAddress.description: The member's billing address (business memberships only). This is optional even for business memberships. If it doesn't exist, assume the billing address is the same as the delivery address.

ClosestLocality.description: The name of the closest locality to the member. Based on the "Closest town" information supplied by the member when creating their account.

ClosestDistrict.description: The name of the closest district to the member. Based on the "Closest town" information supplied by the member when creating their account.

ClosestDistrictId.description: The ID of the closest district to the member. Based on the "Closest town" information supplied by the member when creating their account.

IsAuthenticated.description: Indicates whether the member is authenticated.

IsPayNowAccepted.description: Indicates whether the member can accept Pay Now payments.

FavouriteSearchCount.description: The number of saved searches in the member's favourites.

FavouriteCategoryCount.description: The number of saved categories in the member's favourites.

FavouriteSellerCount.description: The number of saved sellers in the member's favourites.

AutoBillingEnabled.description: Indicates whether the member has set up auto-billing.

CanListClearanceItems.description: Indicates whether the member can list clearance items using the IsClearance flag. This is currently only for certain elite sellers.

IsTopSeller.description: Indicates whether the member is currently a registered top seller.

IsRegisteredWineSeller.description: Indicates whether the member is currently a registered wine seller. This will be false if the member has not registered, or if the registration has been disabled, or if the off-license has expired, or if the member cannot accept Pay Now payments.

IsPropertyAgent.description: Indicates whether the member is registered as a property agent.

IsRentalAgent.description: Indicates whether the member is registered as a rental agent.

IsJobAgent.description: Indicates whether the member is registered as a job agent.

CreditCardType.description: If the user has a saved credit card that they can use, contains the card type ("Visa", "MasterCard", etc). Will be omitted if the user does not have a saved card.

CreditCardLastFourDigits.description: If the user has a saved credit card, contains the last four digits of the card number (e.g. "1234"). Will be omitted if the user does not have a saved card.

CreditCardExpiryMonth.description: If the user has a saved credit card, contains the month when it expires (1 = January, 12 = December).

CreditCardExpiryYear.description: If the user has a saved credit card, contains the year when it expires.

RecentSearchesEnabled.description: Indicates whether recent searches are recorded against the user's profile.

HighVolumeListingCount.description: The number of active listings the member has which contribute towards the high volume threshold. Generally speaking, auctions contribute towards the high volume threshold while classifieds do not. Some categories are exempt; listings within those categories do not count towards the threshold either.

HighVolumeThreshold.description: The user's high volume listing allowance. This is the number of active listings you can have without incurring a high volume listing fee (this fee is charged for each new listing). All classifieds and auctions in some categories are exempt from high volume listing fees.

CanRemoveBids.description:
Indicates whether the member can remove bids using the remove bid API.

                                This field will always return true.

ShoppingCartCount.description: The number of items in the members cart.

IsInTrade.description: Indicates whether the member is a professional trader. If they are a professional trader then their listings are protected by the Consumer Guarantees Act.

Photo.description: A URL representing the member's photo.

ExternalTrackingToken.description: An external tracking token used to uniquely identify a member without exposing member information.

MobilePhoneNumber.description: The member's mobile phone number.

IsFlatShippingCharge.description: Indicates whether one flat shipping fee will be charged if more than one of this item is purchased. Only applicable for Buy Now Only listings.

RemainingGalleryPlusRelists.description: The number of times the item can be relisted and get the gallery promotion for free. This value is only present if you are the seller and the listing had the gallery promotion applied due to the gallery plus promotion. Note that for this field, a value of zero is not the same as if the field is missing (a value of zero means gallery plus is in effect whereas if the field is missing it means that you are not the seller or gallery plus is not in effect).

ExternalReferenceId.description: The external reference ID, if one exists. Only available to the seller of a listing.

SKU.description: SKU or Stock Keeping Unit. Used to uniquely identify an auction's product line.

IsClearance.description: This indicates that the listing is a clearance item. Clearance listings include listings with was/now pricing and general clearance stock.

PercentageOff.description: The percentage that a product has been discounted. This has been rounded for display purposes. This field will only be populated if IsClearance is true.

Options.description: The combination of variant options that this variant represents.

ListingGroupId.description: The identifier of the group of related multi-variant listings. Blank if the listing is not multi-variant

StatusDate.description: The date the status was last changed.

SoldDate.description: The date and time the item was sold.

SoldType.description: The method of sale. Valid values are "Auction", "Buy now" and "Fixed price offer".

SalePrice.description: The price the item was sold for, excluding shipping. If this was a multi-quantity purchase, then this is the price each individual item sold for multiplied by the quantity sold (i.e. the total value of the transaction, minus the shipping cost).

SelectedShipping.description: A description of the selected shipping method (e.g. "$8.00 Nation-wide courier").

BuyerDeliveryAddress.description: The delivery address as indicated by the buyer.

MessageFromBuyer.description: The message from the buyer, if any.

SuccessFees.description: The success fees associated with the sale.

IsPayNowPurchase.description: Indicates whether the buyer has purchased the item using Pay Now. For high risk payments, the value will be false until the payment has been manually approved by the Trade Me customer service team.

IsPaymentPending.description: The current state of the payment

PayNowRefundValue.description: If the item was a Pay Now purchase, the portion of the original purchase price that has been refunded, as a dollar figure. If the value is missing, it may be assumed to be $0 (i.e. the payment was not refunded).

ShippingType.description: The type of shipping that was selected.
x-enum-descriptions: The type of the "None of the options apply to me" shipping option. Do not use when listing an item.
Obsolete. Do not use.

Indicates that the seller will confirm the shipping details with the buyer directly. This shipping option cannot be used when Pay Now is specified as a payment option. When listing an item, this option cannot be used in combination with other shipping options.
Indicates the item can be picked up. Do not use when listing an item (use thePickupfield instead).
Indicates the item can be shipped for free within New Zealand. When listing an item, this option cannot be used in combination with other shipping options.
Custom shipping option. Allows the seller to specify the price and description. Multiple custom shipping options are allowed (up to ten).
Trademe shipping option. Allows the seller to calculate the quotes from couriers, all calculated quotes will be saved in custom shipping options.

HasSellerPlaceFeedback.description: Indicates whether the seller has placed feedback.

HasBuyerPlaceFeedback.description: Indicates whether the buyer has placed feedback.

OfferId.description: The ID of the fixed price offer, if any.

InvoiceId.description: The ID of the associated invoice. Only populated when an invoice is actually generated, which is typically when payment instructions are sent to the buyer.

ReferenceNumber.description: The reference number that the buyer can use when making a deposit into the seller's bank account.

Price.description: The price the item was sold for, excluding shipping. If the purchase was for multiple items, this is the price of a single item.

SubtotalPrice.description: The price for all items, excluding shipping (i.e. equal to SalePrice * QuantitySold).

TotalShippingPrice.description: The total price for shipping. If flat shipping is not enabled, equal to ShippingPrice * QuantitySold.

TotalSalePrice.description: The total price for the entire sale, including shipping. If the purchase was for multiple items, all items are included in this price.

OrderId.description: If the item was purchased via the shopping cart then a purchased cart id is returned which is called order Id.

PaymentMethod.description: The payment method used to purchase this item

This value is only present if you are the seller and the listing had the gallery promotion applied due to the gallery plus promotion. Note that for this field, a value of zero is not the same as if the field is missing (a value of zero means gallery plus is in effect whereas if the field is missing it means that you are not the seller or gallery plus is not in effect).

RegionId.description:
The ID of the region where this item is located. In the general search, listing details and watchlist APIs this is the ID of the seller's region (using the two-tier region/suburb system), which means it might be inconsistent with the region name. In the property search API this is the ID of the property region, using the three-tier region/district/suburb system.

                                This field cannot cope with the two main geographical classification systems.  Except for the property search API, it should not be used.

End.description: The date and time the open home is no longer open for viewing. Must be the same day as Start.

This value is only present if you are the seller and the listing had the gallery promotion applied due to the gallery plus promotion. Note that for this field, a value of zero is not the same as if the field is missing (a value of zero means gallery plus is in effect whereas if the field is missing it means that you are not the seller or gallery plus is not in effect).

Parameters.description: A list of search parameters which are applicable to the searched category. Not returned unless return_metadata is true.

LowerBoundName.description: If the parameter is a ranged parameter, this is the name of the parameter to use to specify the lower bound.

UpperBoundName.description: If the parameter is a ranged parameter, this is the name of the parameter to use to specify the upper bound.

AllowsMultipleValues.description: Indicates the user is allowed to select multiple values. Each value should be comma-separated. Currently applies only to String parameters.

MutualExclusionGroup.description: If present, indicates this parameter is part of a group of parameters which are all mutually exclusive. The group name can be used as a heading name.

DependentOn.description: If present, the Name (not the DisplayName) of another parameter. If the user is filtering by that other parameter, then this filter becomes available for use. The parameter that is referenced will be a single-valued (non-ranged).

ExternalOptionsKey.description: If present, indicates that the list of options is not immediately available, but can be retrieved from the SearchOptions API endpoint. The value is the key that should be passed to the SearchOptions API. Either the list of options is really long, or the list is dependent on the value of another parameter (see the DependentOn field).

Options.description: A list of options to display to the user.

Display.description: What should be displayed for this value (often the same).

DependentParameter.description: Dependent parameter to display cascading structure

DisplaySuggested.description: Indicates this parameter should be displayed by default

DisplayNew.description: Indicates whether this parameter should be displayed with a 'New' tag or not

SortOrders.description: A list of sort orders which are applicable to the searched category. Not returned unless return_metadata is true.

MemberProfile.description: Details of the member that is being filtered on. Not returned unless member_listing is non-zero and return_metadata is true.

IsEnabled.description: Indicates whether the member account is enabled.

DateRemoved.description: The date the member profile was disabled (assuming it has been disabled).

Member.description: The member details associated with this store

MemberId.description: The ID of the member which corresponds to this store.

Nickname.description: The nickname of the member. Some characters may be changed, if we determine it is necessary to protect the member's privacy.

DateAddressVerified.description: The date the member was address verified.

UniqueNegative.description: The number of distinct members who have placed negative feedback against this member.

UniquePositive.description: The number of distinct members who have placed positive feedback against this member.

FeedbackCount.description: The member's total feedback (UniquePositive minus UniqueNegative).

IsAddressVerified.description: Indicates whether the member has been address verified.

IsDealer.description: Indicates whether the member is a car dealer.

IsAuthenticated.description: Indicates whether the member is authenticated.

IsInTrade.description: Indicates whether the member is a professional trader.

ImportChargesMayApply.description: Indicates that the trader is an international seller, and therefore customs import charges may apply.

IsTopSeller.description: Indicates whether the member is currently a Top Seller

IsRentiUser.description: Indicates whether the member is a renti user.

Store.description: Store details, if the seller has been set up as a Trade Me store.

LogoImageUri.description: The URL of a small logo image (180x52).

BannerImageUri.description: The URL of a banner image. Stores extra banner images are 960x120. Store banner images are 633x75. When requesting listing details, only stores extra listings have a banner image.

Promotions.description: A collection of promotional images. Only applies to stores extra.

ImageUri.description: The URL of the promotional image 760x240.

Uri.description: The URL that the promotional image should link to.

AltText.description: The alt text for the promo image.

LargeBannerImage.description: The URL's of a large banner image for each breakpoint, small, medium, large, extra large. When requesting listing details, only stores extra listings have a large banner image.

Small.description: The URL of the promotional image in small size 320x180

Medium.description: The URL of the promotional image in medium size 768x432.

Large.description: The URL of the promotional image in large size 1024x576.

XLarge.description: The URL of the promotional image in extra large size 1440x810.

StorePath.description: A url friendly path for the store, that is unique.

SaleCount.description: The number of on sale listings

Tier.description: The tier ID of a tiered store

StartDate.description: The date the listing was created.

HasHomePageFeature.description: Is this a homepage feature listing?

AsAt.description: The date and time the response was generated on the server.

PictureHref.description: The URL of the primary photo for the listing (if the listing has a photo). By default you'll get a thumbnail-sized photo, but you can control the size of the photo using the photo_size parameter.

HasPayNow.description: Indicates whether the item has Pay Now.

IsNew.description: Indicates whether the item is marked as new.

RegionId.description:
The ID of the region where this item is located. In the general search, listing details and watchlist APIs this is the ID of the seller's region (using the two-tier region/suburb system), which means it might be inconsistent with the region name. In the property search API this is the ID of the property region, using the three-tier region/district/suburb system.

                                This field cannot cope with the two main geographical classification systems.  Except for the property search API, it should not be used.

SuburbId.description: The ID of the suburb where this item is located. Only populated by the property search API, which means it uses the three-tier region/district/suburb system.

Suburb.description: The suburb where the company HQ is located.

PickupLocality.description: The pick-up location details if pick-up is allowed and has been specified.

District.description: The name of the district the property is located in.

BidCount.description: The number of bids on the item.

IsReserveMet.description: Indicates whether the item's reserve has been met.

HasReserve.description: Indicates whether the item has a reserve.

HasBuyNow.description: Indicates whether the item has Buy Now.

NoteDate.description: The date of the note on an item.

ReserveState.description: The flag to display on an item.
x-enum-descriptions: There is no reserve on the item (i.e. the reserve price is the same as the starting price).
The value of the highest bid has exceeded the reserve price.
The value of the highest bid has not reached the reserve price.
The listing cannot have a reserve because bidding is not allowed. This may be because it is a classified or because it is a Buy Now Only auction.

Attributes.description: The attributes for the item that are intended to be displayed on the UI.

DisplayName.description: The name of the attribute, in a form suitable for displaying to users. Not required when selling or editing.

Value.description: Value

IsClassified.description: Indicates whether the item is a classified.

OpenHomes.description: A collection of open home times for this listing. Only applies to open home listings.

Start.description: The date and time the open home is open for viewing. The date must be in the future and it must be less than 56 days from the current date. Specify dates in the UTC time zone.

End.description: The date and time the open home is no longer open for viewing. Must be the same day as Start.

IsBuyNowOnly.description: Indicates whether or not this is a Buy Now Only listing.

RemainingGalleryPlusRelists.description: The number of times the item can be relisted and get the gallery promotion for free. This value is only present if you are the seller and the listing had the gallery promotion applied due to the gallery plus promotion. Note that for this field, a value of zero is not the same as if the field is missing (a value of zero means gallery plus is in effect whereas if the field is missing it means that you are not the seller or gallery plus is not in effect).

IsOnWatchList.description: Indicates whether the item is on the authenticated member's watchlist.

GeographicLocation.description: The geographic location (latitude and longitude) of a property.

Latitude.description: The latitude of the location, in degrees (WGS84).

Longitude.description: The longitude of the location, in degrees (WGS84).

Northing.description: The northing of the location, in metres (NZTM).

Easting.description: The easting of the location, in metres (NZTM).

Accuracy.description: The accuracy of the geographic location (address, street or suburb).
x-enum-descriptions: The accuracy of the geographic location is not known.

The geographic location is accurate to the street level.
The geographic location is accurate to the suburb level.

PriceDisplay.description: The price, in a format suitable for displaying to the user. Some categories may have special pricing rules, e.g. properties may have "Price by negotiation".

TotalReviewCount.description: The total number of user-submitted reviews. Currently only applies to services listings.

PositiveReviewCount.description: The number of user-submitted reviews which are positive (i.e. the user selected the thumbs up graphic when submitting a review). Currently only applies to services listings.

WasPrice.description: The usual price that a product is sold at, or the price before it was marked down. This is always more than the Buy Now price for Auctions, or more than the asking price for Classifieds.This field will only be populated if IsClearance is true.

Parameters.description: A list of search parameters which are applicable to the searched category. Not returned unless return_metadata is true.

LowerBoundName.description: If the parameter is a ranged parameter, this is the name of the parameter to use to specify the lower bound.

UpperBoundName.description: If the parameter is a ranged parameter, this is the name of the parameter to use to specify the upper bound.

AllowsMultipleValues.description: Indicates the user is allowed to select multiple values. Each value should be comma-separated. Currently applies only to String parameters.

MutualExclusionGroup.description: If present, indicates this parameter is part of a group of parameters which are all mutually exclusive. The group name can be used as a heading name.

DependentOn.description: If present, the Name (not the DisplayName) of another parameter. If the user is filtering by that other parameter, then this filter becomes available for use. The parameter that is referenced will be a single-valued (non-ranged).

ExternalOptionsKey.description: If present, indicates that the list of options is not immediately available, but can be retrieved from the SearchOptions API endpoint. The value is the key that should be passed to the SearchOptions API. Either the list of options is really long, or the list is dependent on the value of another parameter (see the DependentOn field).

Options.description: A list of options to display to the user.

Display.description: What should be displayed for this value (often the same).

DependentParameter.description: Dependent parameter to display cascading structure

DisplaySuggested.description: Indicates this parameter should be displayed by default

DisplayNew.description: Indicates whether this parameter should be displayed with a 'New' tag or not

SortOrders.description: A list of sort orders which are applicable to the searched category. Not returned unless return_metadata is true.

MemberProfile.description: Details of the member that is being filtered on. Not returned unless member_listing is non-zero and return_metadata is true.

IsEnabled.description: Indicates whether the member account is enabled.

DateRemoved.description: The date the member profile was disabled (assuming it has been disabled).

Member.description: The member details associated with this store

MemberId.description: The ID of the member which corresponds to this store.

Nickname.description: The nickname of the member. Some characters may be changed, if we determine it is necessary to protect the member's privacy.

DateAddressVerified.description: The date the member was address verified.

UniqueNegative.description: The number of distinct members who have placed negative feedback against this member.

UniquePositive.description: The number of distinct members who have placed positive feedback against this member.

FeedbackCount.description: The member's total feedback (UniquePositive minus UniqueNegative).

IsAddressVerified.description: Indicates whether the member has been address verified.

IsDealer.description: Indicates whether the member is a car dealer.

IsAuthenticated.description: Indicates whether the member is authenticated.

IsInTrade.description: Indicates whether the member is a professional trader.

ImportChargesMayApply.description: Indicates that the trader is an international seller, and therefore customs import charges may apply.

IsTopSeller.description: Indicates whether the member is currently a Top Seller

IsRentiUser.description: Indicates whether the member is a renti user.

Store.description: Store details, if the seller has been set up as a Trade Me store.

LogoImageUri.description: The URL of a small logo image (180x52).

BannerImageUri.description: The URL of a banner image. Stores extra banner images are 960x120. Store banner images are 633x75. When requesting listing details, only stores extra listings have a banner image.

Promotions.description: A collection of promotional images. Only applies to stores extra.

ImageUri.description: The URL of the promotional image 760x240.

Uri.description: The URL that the promotional image should link to.

AltText.description: The alt text for the promo image.

LargeBannerImage.description: The URL's of a large banner image for each breakpoint, small, medium, large, extra large. When requesting listing details, only stores extra listings have a large banner image.

Small.description: The URL of the promotional image in small size 320x180

Medium.description: The URL of the promotional image in medium size 768x432.

Large.description: The URL of the promotional image in large size 1024x576.

XLarge.description: The URL of the promotional image in extra large size 1440x810.

StorePath.description: A url friendly path for the store, that is unique.

SaleCount.description: The number of on sale listings

Tier.description: The tier ID of a tiered store
x-enum-descriptions: Store tier not applicable
Basic tier
Premium tier

IsPropertyAgent.description: Indicates whether the member is registered as a property agent.

SuperFeatures.description: A randomised collection of super features matching the current search

SearchQueryId.description: Search query ID for the search.

FavouriteFrequency.description: The frequency of favourite search selected (e.g. "Deleted: -1", "Daily: 1", "ThreeDays: 3", "Weekly:7") that the FavouriteId property refers to. Only applicable for searches that match one of the authenticated user's favourites.

FavouritePushFrequency.description: The push notification of the favourite search performed, which the FavouriteId property refers to. Only applicable for searches that match one of the authenticated user's favourites.

DisplayTitle.description: The display Title on page. It is usually displayed in an H1 tag.
