AggregateCounts.description: The results of aggregation queries returned from the Search Domain.

Success.description: Indicates whether the operation was successful.

Description.description: The description of the error, if the operation failed.

TotalCount.description: The total number of results in the collection. Can be larger than the number of returned results.

TotalCountTruncated.description: True if the total count of results exceeded the allowed maximum and was truncated.

Page.description: The index of the current page of results (starts at 1).

PageSize.description: The number of results in the current page.

List.description: A list of the results in the current page.

StartDate.description: The date the listing was created.

EndDate.description: The date the listing will end.

HasHomePageFeature.description: Is this a homepage feature listing?

AsAt.description: The date and time the response was generated on the server.

PictureHref.description: The URL of the primary photo for the listing (if the listing has a photo). By default you'll get a thumbnail-sized photo, but you can control the size of the photo using the photo_size parameter.

HasPayNow.description: Indicates whether the item has Pay Now.

IsNew.description: Indicates whether the item is marked as new.

RegionId.description:
The ID of the region where this item is located. In the general search, listing details and watchlist APIs this is the ID of the seller's region (using the two-tier region/suburb system), which means it might be inconsistent with the region name. In the property search API this is the ID of the property region, using the three-tier region/district/suburb system.

                                This field cannot cope with the two main geographical classification systems.  Except for the property search API, it should not be used.

SuburbId.description: The ID of the suburb where this item is located. Only populated by the property search API, which means it uses the three-tier region/district/suburb system.

Suburb.description: The suburb where the company HQ is located.

PickupLocality.description: The pick-up location details if pick-up is allowed and has been specified.

District.description: The name of the district the property is located in.

BidCount.description: The number of bids on the item.

IsReserveMet.description: Indicates whether the item's reserve has been met.

HasReserve.description: Indicates whether the item has a reserve.

HasBuyNow.description: Indicates whether the item has Buy Now.

NoteDate.description: The date of the note on an item.

ReserveState.description: The flag to display on an item.
x-enum-descriptions: There is no reserve on the item (i.e. the reserve price is the same as the starting price).
The value of the highest bid has exceeded the reserve price.
The value of the highest bid has not reached the reserve price.
The listing cannot have a reserve because bidding is not allowed. This may be because it is a classified or because it is a Buy Now Only auction.

Attributes.description: The attributes for the item that are intended to be displayed on the UI.

DisplayName.description: The name of the attribute, in a form suitable for displaying to users. Not required when selling or editing.

Value.description: Value

IsClassified.description: Indicates whether the item is a classified.

OpenHomes.description: A collection of open home times for this listing. Only applies to open home listings.

Start.description: The date and time the open home is open for viewing. The date must be in the future and it must be less than 56 days from the current date. Specify dates in the UTC time zone.

End.description: The date and time the open home is no longer open for viewing. Must be the same day as Start.

IsBuyNowOnly.description: Indicates whether or not this is a Buy Now Only listing.

RemainingGalleryPlusRelists.description: The number of times the item can be relisted and get the gallery promotion for free. This value is only present if you are the seller and the listing had the gallery promotion applied due to the gallery plus promotion. Note that for this field, a value of zero is not the same as if the field is missing (a value of zero means gallery plus is in effect whereas if the field is missing it means that you are not the seller or gallery plus is not in effect).

IsOnWatchList.description: Indicates whether the item is on the authenticated member's watchlist.

GeographicLocation.description: The geographic location (latitude and longitude) of a property.

Latitude.description: The latitude of the location, in degrees (WGS84).

Longitude.description: The longitude of the location, in degrees (WGS84).

Northing.description: The northing of the location, in metres (NZTM).

Easting.description: The easting of the location, in metres (NZTM).

Accuracy.description: The accuracy of the geographic location (address, street or suburb).
x-enum-descriptions: The accuracy of the geographic location is not known.
The geographic location is accurate to the address level.
The geographic location is accurate to the street level.
The geographic location is accurate to the suburb level.
The geographic location is accurate to the AdminPinPoint level.

PriceDisplay.description: The price, in a format suitable for displaying to the user. Some categories may have special pricing rules, e.g. properties may have "Price by negotiation".

TotalReviewCount.description: The total number of user-submitted reviews. Currently only applies to services listings.

PositiveReviewCount.description: The number of user-submitted reviews which are positive (i.e. the user selected the thumbs up graphic when submitting a review). Currently only applies to services listings.

HasAppliedForJob.description: Indicates whether the authenticated member has applied for the job. Only applies for job listings.

JobApplicationDate.description: The date and time of the member's most recent job application, if any. This field will only be populated if HasAppliedForJob is true.

HasFreeShipping.description: Indicates if the listing offers free shipping as an option

IsClearance.description: This indicates that the listing is a clearance item. Clearance listings include listings with was/now pricing and general clearance stock.

WasPrice.description: The usual price that a product is sold at, or the price before it was marked down. This is always more than the Buy Now price for Auctions, or more than the asking price for Classifieds.This field will only be populated if IsClearance is true.

PercentageOff.description: The percentage that a product has been discounted. This has been rounded for display purposes. This field will only be populated if IsClearance is true.

Branding.description: The branding object for the company.

LargeSquareLogo.description: A large square branding image with dimensions of 480x480.

LargeWideLogo.description: A large rectangular branding image with dimensions of 480x200.

BackgroundColor.description: Banner outline/stroke colour, tick the checkbox before saving to apply the new colour

TextColor.description: Banner background colour, tick the checkbox before saving to apply the new colour

StrokeColor.description: Banner text colour, tick the checkbox before saving to apply the new colour

DisableBanner.description: Disable the agent branding regardless of Super Feature status

OfficeLocation.description: The name of the office location

LargeBannerURL.description: The url of a larger version of the logo

IsSuperFeatured.description: Is this a super featured listing?

ShortDescription.description: Short description of a listing. This is Jobs and Services specfic.

PhotoUrls.description: A collection of photo urls for the listing

PromotionId.description: The ID of the promotion applied to this listing.

HasEmbeddedVideo.description: Indicates whether the listing has an embedded video

VariantDefinitionSummary.description: A summary of the variant information.

PriceLow.description: The lowest price of all the variants, if there is a price range.

PriceHigh.description: The highest price of all the variants, if there is a price range.

Price.description: The price of the delivery option; 0 if it's free shipping

HasPriceRange.description: Whether or not the variants have a single price or a price range.

DiscountPercentLow.description: The lowest discount percentage of all the variants, if there is a discount percentage range.

DiscountPercentHigh.description: The highest discount percentage of all the variants, if there is a discount percentage range.

DiscountPercent.description: The discount percentage of all the variants, if they are all the same.

HasDiscountPercentRange.description: Whether or not the variants have a single discount percentage or a discount percentage range.

AllDiscounted.description: Whether or not the variants are all discounted.

AllOnClearance.description: Whether or not the variants are all on clearance.

AdditionalData.description: Structured information for Listing Additional Data

BulletPoints.description: The bullet points for display in the search results

Tags.description: The tags for display in the search results

ListingExtras.description: A collection of extras that are currently applied to the listing

IsLoyaltyEligible.description: Indicates whether the listing is eligible to loyalty program.

HasPing.description: Indicates whether Ping is a supported payment option.

StoreBrandLogoUrl.description: The store seller profile photo Url. This field is populated only if below criterias met - Listing has Gallery or Feature depth products - Listing belongs to a store - Store has a tier where store brand logo feature has turned on

WhyPayPrice.description: The why pay marketing price that is supplied by the deal provider when they create listings for our deal channel.

Has3DTour.description: Indicates whether the listing has a 3D Tour

ShippingDetails.description: Shipping details for the current listing. Null if no shipping details available.

ShippingTemplateId.description: Represents the template used to create the shipping options on this listing

SuggestedShipping.description: Suggested shipping details, based on member preferences.

Destination.description: Name of the shipping destination, if structured shipping information exists.

DeliveryTime.description: Delivery time details for the current listing, if structured shipping information exists.

MinValue.description: The earliest expected delivery time returned in ISO 8601 duration format.

MaxValue.description: The latest expected delivery time returned in ISO 8601 duration format.

IsRural.description: Indicates if the SuggestedShipping option is for rural delivery, if structured shipping information exists.

PriceType.description: Indicates the price type of boat and farming machinery listings
x-enum-descriptions: Asking Price.
Price On Application.
Excluding GST.

HasSpecialOffer.description: Indicates whether there is a special offer for motors and farming machinery listings

NewCarInformation.description: Information specific to new cars if the current listing is a new car listing.

Availability.description: Enum value denoting the availability of the car, can be : 'inTransit' , 'availableToOrder'

New car is available to order

Indicates that this car is an ex-demo
New car is certified pre owned

LogoUrl.description: Url of the certified preowned programme's logo (designed for a light background).

DarkModeLogoUrl.description: Url of the certified preowned programme's logo (designed for a dark background).

LastServiceReview.description: Latest positive review for a super feature addons. Null if no positive review available.

ServiceReviewerNickname.description: Latest positive service reviewer's nick name

Sponsored.description: listing’s required metadata relating to Sponsored Listings.

TopSortProductId.description: The ID for the Tradevine (and thus TopSort) Product that the listing is related to.

TopSortResolveBidId.description: TopSort ID for the bid that has won the sponsorship auction.

TopSortUniqueId.description: Unique ID derived from the TopSort ID that is sent to TopSort for each impression / click

MotorsExternalMediaOverview.description: An overview of what motors external media information exists.

HasInstavid360Spinner.description: Whether the listing has data for an Instavid 360 spinner.

The buyer cannot pickup the item (delivery only).

Parameters.description: A list of search parameters which are applicable to the searched category. Not returned unless return_metadata is true.

LowerBoundName.description: If the parameter is a ranged parameter, this is the name of the parameter to use to specify the lower bound.

UpperBoundName.description: If the parameter is a ranged parameter, this is the name of the parameter to use to specify the upper bound.

AllowsMultipleValues.description: Indicates the user is allowed to select multiple values. Each value should be comma-separated. Currently applies only to String parameters.

MutualExclusionGroup.description: If present, indicates this parameter is part of a group of parameters which are all mutually exclusive. The group name can be used as a heading name.

DependentOn.description: If present, the Name (not the DisplayName) of another parameter. If the user is filtering by that other parameter, then this filter becomes available for use. The parameter that is referenced will be a single-valued (non-ranged).

ExternalOptionsKey.description: If present, indicates that the list of options is not immediately available, but can be retrieved from the SearchOptions API endpoint. The value is the key that should be passed to the SearchOptions API. Either the list of options is really long, or the list is dependent on the value of another parameter (see the DependentOn field).

Options.description: A list of options to display to the user.

Display.description: What should be displayed for this value (often the same).

DependentParameter.description: Dependent parameter to display cascading structure

DisplaySuggested.description: Indicates this parameter should be displayed by default

DisplayNew.description: Indicates whether this parameter should be displayed with a 'New' tag or not

SortOrders.description: A list of sort orders which are applicable to the searched category. Not returned unless return_metadata is true.

MemberProfile.description: Details of the member that is being filtered on. Not returned unless member_listing is non-zero and return_metadata is true.

IsEnabled.description: Indicates whether the member account is enabled.

DateRemoved.description: The date the member profile was disabled (assuming it has been disabled).

Member.description: The member details associated with this store

MemberId.description: The ID of the member which corresponds to this store.

Nickname.description: The nickname of the member. Some characters may be changed, if we determine it is necessary to protect the member's privacy.

DateAddressVerified.description: The date the member was address verified.

UniqueNegative.description: The number of distinct members who have placed negative feedback against this member.

UniquePositive.description: The number of distinct members who have placed positive feedback against this member.

FeedbackCount.description: The member's total feedback (UniquePositive minus UniqueNegative).

AltText.description: The alt text for the promo image.

LargeBannerImage.description: The URL's of a large banner image for each breakpoint, small, medium, large, extra large. When requesting listing details, only stores extra listings have a large banner image.

Medium.description: The URL of the promotional image in medium size 768x432.

Large.description: The URL of the promotional image in large size 1024x576.

XLarge.description: The URL of the promotional image in extra large size 1440x810.

StorePath.description: A url friendly path for the store, that is unique.

SaleCount.description: The number of on sale listings

Tier.description: The tier ID of a tiered store

Basic tier

IsPropertyAgent.description: Indicates whether the member is registered as a property agent.

SuperFeatures.description: A randomised collection of super features matching the current search

SearchQueryId.description: Search query ID for the search.

FavouriteFrequency.description: The frequency of favourite search selected (e.g. "Deleted: -1", "Daily: 1", "ThreeDays: 3", "Weekly:7") that the FavouriteId property refers to. Only applicable for searches that match one of the authenticated user's favourites.

AggregateCounts.description: The results of aggregation queries returned from the Search Domain.

TotalCount.description: The total number of results in the collection. Can be larger than the number of returned results.

TotalCountTruncated.description: True if the total count of results exceeded the allowed maximum and was truncated.

Page.description: The index of the current page of results (starts at 1).

PageSize.description: The number of results in the current page.

List.description: A list of the results in the current page.

StartDate.description: The date the listing was created.

EndDate.description: The date the listing will end.

HasHomePageFeature.description: Is this a homepage feature listing?

AsAt.description: The date and time the response was generated on the server.

PictureHref.description: The URL of the primary photo for the listing (if the listing has a photo). By default you'll get a thumbnail-sized photo, but you can control the size of the photo using the photo_size parameter.

HasPayNow.description: Indicates whether the item has Pay Now.

IsNew.description: Indicates whether the item is marked as new.

RegionId.description:
The ID of the region where this item is located. In the general search, listing details and watchlist APIs this is the ID of the seller's region (using the two-tier region/suburb system), which means it might be inconsistent with the region name. In the property search API this is the ID of the property region, using the three-tier region/district/suburb system.

                                This field cannot cope with the two main geographical classification systems.  Except for the property search API, it should not be used.

SuburbId.description: The ID of the suburb where this item is located. Only populated by the property search API, which means it uses the three-tier region/district/suburb system.

Suburb.description: The suburb where the company HQ is located.

PickupLocality.description: The pick-up location details if pick-up is allowed and has been specified.

District.description: The name of the district the property is located in.

BidCount.description: The number of bids on the item.

IsReserveMet.description: Indicates whether the item's reserve has been met.

HasReserve.description: Indicates whether the item has a reserve.

HasBuyNow.description: Indicates whether the item has Buy Now.

NoteDate.description: The date of the note on an item.

ReserveState.description: The flag to display on an item.
x-enum-descriptions: There is no reserve on the item (i.e. the reserve price is the same as the starting price).
The value of the highest bid has exceeded the reserve price.
The value of the highest bid has not reached the reserve price.
The listing cannot have a reserve because bidding is not allowed. This may be because it is a classified or because it is a Buy Now Only auction.

Attributes.description: The attributes for the item that are intended to be displayed on the UI.

DisplayName.description: The name of the attribute, in a form suitable for displaying to users. Not required when selling or editing.

Value.description: Value

IsClassified.description: Indicates whether the item is a classified.

OpenHomes.description: A collection of open home times for this listing. Only applies to open home listings.

Start.description: The date and time the open home is open for viewing. The date must be in the future and it must be less than 56 days from the current date. Specify dates in the UTC time zone.

End.description: The date and time the open home is no longer open for viewing. Must be the same day as Start.

IsBuyNowOnly.description: Indicates whether or not this is a Buy Now Only listing.

RemainingGalleryPlusRelists.description: The number of times the item can be relisted and get the gallery promotion for free. This value is only present if you are the seller and the listing had the gallery promotion applied due to the gallery plus promotion. Note that for this field, a value of zero is not the same as if the field is missing (a value of zero means gallery plus is in effect whereas if the field is missing it means that you are not the seller or gallery plus is not in effect).

IsOnWatchList.description: Indicates whether the item is on the authenticated member's watchlist.

GeographicLocation.description: The geographic location (latitude and longitude) of a property.

Latitude.description: The latitude of the location, in degrees (WGS84).

Longitude.description: The longitude of the location, in degrees (WGS84).

Northing.description: The northing of the location, in metres (NZTM).

Easting.description: The easting of the location, in metres (NZTM).

Accuracy.description: The accuracy of the geographic location (address, street or suburb).
x-enum-descriptions: The accuracy of the geographic location is not known.
The geographic location is accurate to the address level.
The geographic location is accurate to the street level.
The geographic location is accurate to the suburb level.
The geographic location is accurate to the AdminPinPoint level.

PriceDisplay.description: The price, in a format suitable for displaying to the user. Some categories may have special pricing rules, e.g. properties may have "Price by negotiation".

TotalReviewCount.description: The total number of user-submitted reviews. Currently only applies to services listings.

PositiveReviewCount.description: The number of user-submitted reviews which are positive (i.e. the user selected the thumbs up graphic when submitting a review). Currently only applies to services listings.

HasAppliedForJob.description: Indicates whether the authenticated member has applied for the job. Only applies for job listings.

JobApplicationDate.description: The date and time of the member's most recent job application, if any. This field will only be populated if HasAppliedForJob is true.

HasFreeShipping.description: Indicates if the listing offers free shipping as an option

IsClearance.description: This indicates that the listing is a clearance item. Clearance listings include listings with was/now pricing and general clearance stock.

WasPrice.description: The usual price that a product is sold at, or the price before it was marked down. This is always more than the Buy Now price for Auctions, or more than the asking price for Classifieds.This field will only be populated if IsClearance is true.

PercentageOff.description: The percentage that a product has been discounted. This has been rounded for display purposes. This field will only be populated if IsClearance is true.

Branding.description: The branding object for the company.

LargeSquareLogo.description: A large square branding image with dimensions of 480x480.

LargeWideLogo.description: A large rectangular branding image with dimensions of 480x200.

BackgroundColor.description: Banner outline/stroke colour, tick the checkbox before saving to apply the new colour

TextColor.description: Banner background colour, tick the checkbox before saving to apply the new colour

DisableBanner.description: Disable the agent branding regardless of Super Feature status

OfficeLocation.description: The name of the office location

LargeBannerURL.description: The url of a larger version of the logo

IsSuperFeatured.description: Is this a super featured listing?

ShortDescription.description: Short description of a listing. This is Jobs and Services specfic.

PhotoUrls.description: A collection of photo urls for the listing

PromotionId.description: The ID of the promotion applied to this listing.

HasEmbeddedVideo.description: Indicates whether the listing has an embedded video

Price.description: The price of the delivery option; 0 if it's free shipping

WhyPayPrice.description: The why pay marketing price that is supplied by the deal provider when they create listings for our deal channel.

Has3DTour.description: Indicates whether the listing has a 3D Tour

ShippingDetails.description: Shipping details for the current listing. Null if no shipping details available.

ShippingTemplateId.description: Represents the template used to create the shipping options on this listing

SuggestedShipping.description: Suggested shipping details, based on member preferences.

RegionId.description:
The ID of the region where this item is located. In the general search, listing details and watchlist APIs this is the ID of the seller's region (using the two-tier region/suburb system), which means it might be inconsistent with the region name. In the property search API this is the ID of the property region, using the three-tier region/district/suburb system.

                                This field cannot cope with the two main geographical classification systems.  Except for the property search API, it should not be used.

Parameters.description: A list of search parameters which are applicable to the searched category. Not returned unless return_metadata is true.

LowerBoundName.description: If the parameter is a ranged parameter, this is the name of the parameter to use to specify the lower bound.

UpperBoundName.description: If the parameter is a ranged parameter, this is the name of the parameter to use to specify the upper bound.

AllowsMultipleValues.description: Indicates the user is allowed to select multiple values. Each value should be comma-separated. Currently applies only to String parameters.

MutualExclusionGroup.description: If present, indicates this parameter is part of a group of parameters which are all mutually exclusive. The group name can be used as a heading name.

DependentOn.description: If present, the Name (not the DisplayName) of another parameter. If the user is filtering by that other parameter, then this filter becomes available for use. The parameter that is referenced will be a single-valued (non-ranged).

ExternalOptionsKey.description: If present, indicates that the list of options is not immediately available, but can be retrieved from the SearchOptions API endpoint. The value is the key that should be passed to the SearchOptions API. Either the list of options is really long, or the list is dependent on the value of another parameter (see the DependentOn field).

Options.description: A list of options to display to the user.

Display.description: What should be displayed for this value (often the same).

DependentParameter.description: Dependent parameter to display cascading structure

DisplaySuggested.description: Indicates this parameter should be displayed by default

DisplayNew.description: Indicates whether this parameter should be displayed with a 'New' tag or not

Parameters.description: A list of search parameters which are applicable to the searched category. Not returned unless return_metadata is true.

LowerBoundName.description: If the parameter is a ranged parameter, this is the name of the parameter to use to specify the lower bound.

UpperBoundName.description: If the parameter is a ranged parameter, this is the name of the parameter to use to specify the upper bound.

AllowsMultipleValues.description: Indicates the user is allowed to select multiple values. Each value should be comma-separated. Currently applies only to String parameters.

MutualExclusionGroup.description: If present, indicates this parameter is part of a group of parameters which are all mutually exclusive. The group name can be used as a heading name.

DependentOn.description: If present, the Name (not the DisplayName) of another parameter. If the user is filtering by that other parameter, then this filter becomes available for use. The parameter that is referenced will be a single-valued (non-ranged).

ExternalOptionsKey.description: If present, indicates that the list of options is not immediately available, but can be retrieved from the SearchOptions API endpoint. The value is the key that should be passed to the SearchOptions API. Either the list of options is really long, or the list is dependent on the value of another parameter (see the DependentOn field).

Options.description: A list of options to display to the user.

Display.description: What should be displayed for this value (often the same).

DependentParameter.description: Dependent parameter to display cascading structure

DisplaySuggested.description: Indicates this parameter should be displayed by default

DisplayNew.description: Indicates whether this parameter should be displayed with a 'New' tag or not

HasPayNow.description: Indicates whether the item has Pay Now.

IsNew.description: Indicates whether the item is marked as new.

RegionId.description:
The ID of the region where this item is located. In the general search, listing details and watchlist APIs this is the ID of the seller's region (using the two-tier region/suburb system), which means it might be inconsistent with the region name. In the property search API this is the ID of the property region, using the three-tier region/district/suburb system.

                                This field cannot cope with the two main geographical classification systems.  Except for the property search API, it should not be used.

SuburbId.description: The ID of the suburb where this item is located. Only populated by the property search API, which means it uses the three-tier region/district/suburb system.

Suburb.description: The suburb where the company HQ is located.

PickupLocality.description: The pick-up location details if pick-up is allowed and has been specified.

BidCount.description: The number of bids on the item.

HasReserve.description: Indicates whether the item has a reserve.

HasBuyNow.description: Indicates whether the item has Buy Now.

NoteDate.description: The date of the note on an item.

ReserveState.description: The flag to display on an item.
x-enum-descriptions: There is no reserve on the item (i.e. the reserve price is the same as the starting price).
The value of the highest bid has exceeded the reserve price.
The value of the highest bid has not reached the reserve price.
The listing cannot have a reserve because bidding is not allowed. This may be because it is a classified or because it is a Buy Now Only auction.

Attributes.description: The attributes for the item that are intended to be displayed on the UI.

DisplayName.description: The name of the attribute, in a form suitable for displaying to users. Not required when selling or editing.

Value.description: Value

IsClassified.description: Indicates whether the item is a classified.

OpenHomes.description: A collection of open home times for this listing. Only applies to open home listings.

Start.description: The date and time the open home is open for viewing. The date must be in the future and it must be less than 56 days from the current date. Specify dates in the UTC time zone.

End.description: The date and time the open home is no longer open for viewing. Must be the same day as Start.

IsBuyNowOnly.description: Indicates whether or not this is a Buy Now Only listing.

RemainingGalleryPlusRelists.description: The number of times the item can be relisted and get the gallery promotion for free. This value is only present if you are the seller and the listing had the gallery promotion applied due to the gallery plus promotion. Note that for this field, a value of zero is not the same as if the field is missing (a value of zero means gallery plus is in effect whereas if the field is missing it means that you are not the seller or gallery plus is not in effect).

IsOnWatchList.description: Indicates whether the item is on the authenticated member's watchlist.

GeographicLocation.description: The geographic location (latitude and longitude) of a property.

Longitude.description: The longitude of the location, in degrees (WGS84).

Northing.description: The northing of the location, in metres (NZTM).

Easting.description: The easting of the location, in metres (NZTM).

The geographic location is accurate to the suburb level.
The geographic location is accurate to the AdminPinPoint level.

Parameters.description: A list of search parameters which are applicable to the searched category. Not returned unless return_metadata is true.

LowerBoundName.description: If the parameter is a ranged parameter, this is the name of the parameter to use to specify the lower bound.

MutualExclusionGroup.description: If present, indicates this parameter is part of a group of parameters which are all mutually exclusive. The group name can be used as a heading name.

DependentOn.description: If present, the Name (not the DisplayName) of another parameter. If the user is filtering by that other parameter, then this filter becomes available for use. The parameter that is referenced will be a single-valued (non-ranged).

ExternalOptionsKey.description: If present, indicates that the list of options is not immediately available, but can be retrieved from the SearchOptions API endpoint. The value is the key that should be passed to the SearchOptions API. Parameters.description: A list of search parameters which are applicable to the searched category. Not returned unless return_metadata is true.

LowerBoundName.description: If the parameter is a ranged parameter, this is the name of the parameter to use to specify the lower bound.

UpperBoundName.description: If the parameter is a ranged parameter, this is the name of the parameter to use to specify the upper bound.

AllowsMultipleValues.description: Indicates the user is allowed to select multiple values. Each value should be comma-separated. Currently applies only to String parameters.

MutualExclusionGroup.description: If present, indicates this parameter is part of a group of parameters which are all mutually exclusive. The group name can be used as a heading name.

DependentOn.description: If present, the Name (not the DisplayName) of another parameter. If the user is filtering by that other parameter, then this filter becomes available for use. The parameter that is referenced will be a single-valued (non-ranged).

ExternalOptionsKey.description: If present, indicates that the list of options is not immediately available, but can be retrieved from the SearchOptions API endpoint. The value is the key that should be passed to the SearchOptions API. Either the list of options is really long, or the list is dependent on the value of another parameter (see the DependentOn field).

Parameters.description: A list of search parameters which are applicable to the searched category. Not returned unless return_metadata is true.

LowerBoundName.description: If the parameter is a ranged parameter, this is the name of the parameter to use to specify the lower bound.

UpperBoundName.description: If the parameter is a ranged parameter, this is the name of the parameter to use to specify the upper bound.

AllowsMultipleValues.description: Indicates the user is allowed to select multiple values. Each value should be comma-separated. Currently applies only to String parameters.

MutualExclusionGroup.description: If present, indicates this parameter is part of a group of parameters which are all mutually exclusive. The group name can be used as a heading name.

DependentOn.description: If present, the Name (not the DisplayName) of another parameter. If the user is filtering by that other parameter, then this filter becomes available for use. The parameter that is referenced will be a single-valued (non-ranged).

ExternalOptionsKey.description: If present, indicates that the list of options is not immediately available, but can be retrieved from the SearchOptions API endpoint. The value is the key that should be passed to the SearchOptions API. Either the list of options is really long, or the list is dependent on the value of another parameter (see the DependentOn field).

Options.description: A list of options to display to the user.

Display.description: What should be displayed for this value (often the same).

DependentParameter.description: Dependent parameter to display cascading structure

DisplaySuggested.description: Indicates this parameter should be displayed by default

DisplayNew.description: Indicates whether this parameter should be displayed with a 'New' tag or not

SortOrders.description: A list of sort orders which are applicable to the searched category. Not returned unless return_metadata is true.

MemberProfile.description: Details of the member that is being filtered on. Not returned unless member_listing is non-zero and return_metadata is true.

IsEnabled.description: Indicates whether the member account is enabled.

DateRemoved.description: The date the member profile was disabled (assuming it has been disabled).

Member.description: The member details associated with this store

MemberId.description: The ID of the member which corresponds to this store.

Nickname.description: The nickname of the member. Some characters may be changed, if we determine it is necessary to protect the member's privacy.

DateAddressVerified.description: The date the member was address verified.

UniqueNegative.description: The number of distinct members who have placed negative feedback against this member.

UniquePositive.description: The number of distinct members who have placed positive feedback against this member.

FeedbackCount.description: The member's total feedback (UniquePositive minus UniqueNegative).

IsAddressVerified.description: Indicates whether the member has been address verified.

IsDealer.description: Indicates whether the member is a car dealer.

IsAuthenticated.description: Indicates whether the member is authenticated.

IsInTrade.description: Indicates whether the member is a professional trader.

ImportChargesMayApply.description: Indicates that the trader is an international seller, and therefore customs import charges may apply.

IsTopSeller.description: Indicates whether the member is currently a Top Seller

IsRentiUser.description: Indicates whether the member is a renti user.

Store.description: Store details, if the seller has been set up as a Trade Me store.

LogoImageUri.description: The URL of a small logo image (180x52).

BannerImageUri.description: The URL of a banner image. Stores extra banner images are 960x120. Store banner images are 633x75. When requesting listing details, only stores extra listings have a banner image.

Promotions.description: A collection of promotional images. Only applies to stores extra.

ImageUri.description: The URL of the promotional image 760x240.

Uri.description: The URL that the promotional image should link to.

AltText.description: The alt text for the promo image.

LargeBannerImage.description: The URL's of a large banner image for each breakpoint, small, medium, large, extra large. When requesting listing details, only stores extra listings have a large banner image.

Small.description: The URL of the promotional image in small size 320x180

Medium.description: The URL of the promotional image in medium size 768x432.

Large.description: The URL of the promotional image in large size 1024x576.

XLarge.description: The URL of the promotional image in extra large size 1440x810.

StorePath.description: A url friendly path for the store, that is unique.

SaleCount.description: The number of on sale listings

Tier.description: The tier ID of a tiered store

SuperFeatures.description: A randomised collection of super features matching the current search

SearchQueryId.description: Search query ID for the search.

FavouriteFrequency.description: The frequency of favourite search selected (e.g. "Deleted: -1", "Daily: 1", "ThreeDays: 3", "Weekly:7") that the FavouriteId property refers to. Only applicable for searches that match one of the authenticated user's favourites.

FavouritePushFrequency.description: The push notification of the favourite search performed, which the FavouriteId property refers to. Only applicable for searches that match one of the authenticated user's favourites.

DisplayTitle.description: The display Title on page. It is usually displayed in an H1 tag.

AggregateCounts.description: The results of aggregation queries returned from the Search Domain.

TotalCount.description: The total number of results in the collection. Can be larger than the number of returned results.

TotalCountTruncated.description: True if the total count of results exceeded the allowed maximum and was truncated.

Page.description: The index of the current page of results (starts at 1).

PageSize.description: The number of results in the current page.

List.description: A list of the results in the current page.

StartDate.description: The date the listing was created.

EndDate.description: The date the listing will end.

HasHomePageFeature.description: Is this a homepage feature listing?

AsAt.description: The date and time the response was generated on the server.

PictureHref.description: The URL of the primary photo for the listing (if the listing has a photo). By default you'll get a thumbnail-sized photo, but you can control the size of the photo using the photo_size parameter.

HasPayNow.description: Indicates whether the item has Pay Now.

IsNew.description: Indicates whether the item is marked as new.

RegionId.description:
The ID of the region where this item is located. In the general search, listing details and watchlist APIs this is the ID of the seller's region (using the two-tier region/suburb system), which means it might be inconsistent with the region name. In the property search API this is the ID of the property region, using the three-tier region/district/suburb system.

                                This field cannot cope with the two main geographical classification systems.  Except for the property search API, it should not be used.

SuburbId.description: The ID of the suburb where this item is located. Only populated by the property search API, which means it uses the three-tier region/district/suburb system.

Suburb.description: The suburb where the company HQ is located.

PickupLocality.description: The pick-up location details if pick-up is allowed and has been specified.

District.description: The name of the district the property is located in.

BidCount.description: The number of bids on the item.

IsReserveMet.description: Indicates whether the item's reserve has been met.

HasReserve.description: Indicates whether the item has a reserve.

HasBuyNow.description: Indicates whether the item has Buy Now.

NoteDate.description: The date of the note on an item.

ReserveState.description: The flag to display on an item.
x-enum-descriptions: There is no reserve on the item (i.e. the reserve price is the same as the starting price).
The value of the highest bid has exceeded the reserve price.
The value of the highest bid has not reached the reserve price.
The listing cannot have a reserve because bidding is not allowed. This may be because it is a classified or because it is a Buy Now Only auction.

Attributes.description: The attributes for the item that are intended to be displayed on the UI.

DisplayName.description: The name of the attribute, in a form suitable for displaying to users. Not required when selling or editing.

Value.description: Value

IsClassified.description: Indicates whether the item is a classified.

OpenHomes.description: A collection of open home times for this listing. Only applies to open home listings.

Start.description: The date and time the open home is open for viewing. The date must be in the future and it must be less than 56 days from the current date. Specify dates in the UTC time zone.

End.description: The date and time the open home is no longer open for viewing. Must be the same day as Start.

IsBuyNowOnly.description: Indicates whether or not this is a Buy Now Only listing.

RemainingGalleryPlusRelists.description: The number of times the item can be relisted and get the gallery promotion for free. This value is only present if you are the seller and the listing had the gallery promotion applied due to the gallery plus promotion. Note that for this field, a value of zero is not the same as if the field is missing (a value of zero means gallery plus is in effect whereas if the field is missing it means that you are not the seller or gallery plus is not in effect).

IsOnWatchList.description: Indicates whether the item is on the authenticated member's watchlist.

GeographicLocation.description: The geographic location (latitude and longitude) of a property.

Latitude.description: The latitude of the location, in degrees (WGS84).

Longitude.description: The longitude of the location, in degrees (WGS84).

Northing.description: The northing of the location, in metres (NZTM).

Easting.description: The easting of the location, in metres (NZTM).

Accuracy.description: The accuracy of the geographic location (address, street or suburb).
x-enum-descriptions: The accuracy of the geographic location is not known.
The geographic location is accurate to the address level.
The geographic location is accurate to the street level.
The geographic location is accurate to the suburb level.
The geographic location is accurate to the AdminPinPoint level.

PriceDisplay.description: The price, in a format suitable for displaying to the user. Some categories may have special pricing rules, e.g. properties may have "Price by negotiation".

TotalReviewCount.description: The total number of user-submitted reviews. Currently only applies to services listings.

PositiveReviewCount.description: The number of user-submitted reviews which are positive (i.e. the user selected the thumbs up graphic when submitting a review). Currently only applies to services listings.

HasAppliedForJob.description: Indicates whether the authenticated member has applied for the job. Only applies for job listings.

JobApplicationDate.description: The date and time of the member's most recent job application, if any. This field will only be populated if HasAppliedForJob is true.

HasFreeShipping.description: Indicates if the listing offers free shipping as an option

IsClearance.description: This indicates that the listing is a clearance item. Clearance listings include listings with was/now pricing and general clearance stock.

WasPrice.description: The usual price that a product is sold at, or the price before it was marked down. This is always more than the Buy Now price for Auctions, or more than the asking price for Classifieds.This field will only be populated if IsClearance is true.

PercentageOff.description: The percentage that a product has been discounted. This has been rounded for display purposes. This field will only be populated if IsClearance is true.

Branding.description: The branding object for the company.

LargeSquareLogo.description: A large square branding image with dimensions of 480x480.

LargeWideLogo.description: A large rectangular branding image with dimensions of 480x200.

BackgroundColor.description: Banner outline/stroke colour, tick the checkbox before saving to apply the new colour

TextColor.description: Banner background colour, tick the checkbox before saving to apply the new colour

StrokeColor.description: Banner text colour, tick the checkbox before saving to apply the new colour

DisableBanner.description: Disable the agent branding regardless of Super Feature status

OfficeLocation.description: The name of the office location

LargeBannerURL.description: The url of a larger version of the logo

IsSuperFeatured.description: Is this a super featured listing?

ShortDescription.description: Short description of a listing. This is Jobs and Services specfic.

PhotoUrls.description: A collection of photo urls for the listing

PromotionId.description: The ID of the promotion applied to this listing.

HasEmbeddedVideo.description: Indicates whether the listing has an embedded video

VariantDefinitionSummary.description: A summary of the variant information.

PriceLow.description: The lowest price of all the variants, if there is a price range.

PriceHigh.description: The highest price of all the variants, if there is a price range.

Price.description: The price of the delivery option; 0 if it's free shipping

HasPriceRange.description: Whether or not the variants have a single price or a price range.

DiscountPercentLow.description: The lowest discount percentage of all the variants, if there is a discount percentage range.

DiscountPercentHigh.description: The highest discount percentage of all the variants, if there is a discount percentage range.

DiscountPercent.description: The discount percentage of all the variants, if they are all the same.

HasDiscountPercentRange.description: Whether or not the variants have a single discount percentage or a discount percentage range.

AllDiscounted.description: Whether or not the variants are all discounted.

AllOnClearance.description: Whether or not the variants are all on clearance.

AdditionalData.description: Structured information for Listing Additional Data

BulletPoints.description: The bullet points for display in the search results

Tags.description: The tags for display in the search results

ListingExtras.description: A collection of extras that are currently applied to the listing

IsLoyaltyEligible.description: Indicates whether the listing is eligible to loyalty program.

HasPing.description: Indicates whether Ping is a supported payment option.

StoreBrandLogoUrl.description: The store seller profile photo Url. This field is populated only if below criterias met - Listing has Gallery or Feature depth products - Listing belongs to a store - Store has a tier where store brand logo feature has turned on

WhyPayPrice.description: The why pay marketing price that is supplied by the deal provider when they create listings for our deal channel.

Has3DTour.description: Indicates whether the listing has a 3D Tour

ShippingDetails.description: Shipping details for the current listing. Null if no shipping details available.

ShippingTemplateId.description: Represents the template used to create the shipping options on this listing

SuggestedShipping.description: Suggested shipping details, based on member preferences.

Destination.description: Name of the shipping destination, if structured shipping information exists.

DeliveryTime.description: Delivery time details for the current listing, if structured shipping information exists.

MinValue.description: The earliest expected delivery time returned in ISO 8601 duration format.

MaxValue.description: The latest expected delivery time returned in ISO 8601 duration format.

IsRural.description: Indicates if the SuggestedShipping option is for rural delivery, if structured shipping information exists.

ServiceReviewerNickname.description: Latest positive service reviewer's nick name

IsNew.description: Indicates whether the item is marked as new.

RegionId.description:
The ID of the region where this item is located. In the general search, listing details and watchlist APIs this is the ID of the seller's region (using the two-tier region/suburb system), which means it might be inconsistent with the region name. In the property search API this is the ID of the property region, using the three-tier region/district/suburb system.

                                This field cannot cope with the two main geographical classification systems.  Except for the property search API, it should not be used.

This value is only present if you are the seller and the listing had the gallery promotion applied due to the gallery plus promotion. Note that for this field, a value of zero is not the same as if the field is missing (a value of zero means gallery plus is in effect whereas if the field is missing it means that you are not the seller or gallery plus is not in effect).

Parameters.description: A list of search parameters which are applicable to the searched category. Not returned unless return_metadata is true.

LowerBoundName.description: If the parameter is a ranged parameter, this is the name of the parameter to use to specify the lower bound.

UpperBoundName.description: If the parameter is a ranged parameter, this is the name of the parameter to use to specify the upper bound.

AllowsMultipleValues.description: Indicates the user is allowed to select multiple values. Each value should be comma-separated. Currently applies only to String parameters.

MutualExclusionGroup.description: If present, indicates this parameter is part of a group of parameters which are all mutually exclusive. The group name can be used as a heading name.

DependentOn.description: If present, the Name (not the DisplayName) of another parameter. If the user is filtering by that other parameter, then this filter becomes available for use. The parameter that is referenced will be a single-valued (non-ranged).

ExternalOptionsKey.description: If present, indicates that the list of options is not immediately available, but can be retrieved from the SearchOptions API endpoint. The value is the key that should be passed to the SearchOptions API. Either the list of options is really long, or the list is dependent on the value of another parameter (see the DependentOn field).

Parameters.description: A list of search parameters which are applicable to the searched category. Not returned unless return_metadata is true.

LowerBoundName.description: If the parameter is a ranged parameter, this is the name of the parameter to use to specify the lower bound.

UpperBoundName.description: If the parameter is a ranged parameter, this is the name of the parameter to use to specify the upper bound.

AllowsMultipleValues.description: Indicates the user is allowed to select multiple values. Each value should be comma-separated. Currently applies only to String parameters.

MutualExclusionGroup.description: If present, indicates this parameter is part of a group of parameters which are all mutually exclusive. The group name can be used as a heading name.

DependentOn.description: If present, the Name (not the DisplayName) of another parameter. If the user is filtering by that other parameter, then this filter becomes available for use. The parameter that is referenced will be a single-valued (non-ranged).

ExternalOptionsKey.description: If present, indicates that the list of options is not immediately available, but can be retrieved from the SearchOptions API endpoint. The value is the key that should be passed to the SearchOptions API. Either the list of options is really long, or the list is dependent on the value of another parameter (see the DependentOn field).

RegionId.description:
The ID of the region where this item is located. In the general search, listing details and watchlist APIs this is the ID of the seller's region (using the two-tier region/suburb system), which means it might be inconsistent with the region name. In the property search API this is the ID of the property region, using the three-tier region/district/suburb system.

                                This field cannot cope with the two main geographical classification systems.  Except for the property search API, it should not be used.

End.description: The date and time the open home is no longer open for viewing. Must be the same day as Start.

This value is only present if you are the seller and the listing had the gallery promotion applied due to the gallery plus promotion. Note that for this field, a value of zero is not the same as if the field is missing (a value of zero means gallery plus is in effect whereas if the field is missing it means that you are not the seller or gallery plus is not in effect).

Basic tier
Premium tier

IsPropertyAgent.description: Indicates whether the member is registered as a property agent.

SuperFeatures.description: A randomised collection of super features matching the current search

SearchQueryId.description: Search query ID for the search.

FavouriteFrequency.description: The frequency of favourite search selected (e.g. "Deleted: -1", "Daily: 1", "ThreeDays: 3", "Weekly:7") that the FavouriteId property refers to. Only applicable for searches that match one of the authenticated user's favourites.

FavouritePushFrequency.description: The push notification of the favourite search performed, which the FavouriteId property refers to. Only applicable for searches that match one of the authenticated user's favourites.
x-enum-descriptions: Push not enabled for this favourite.
Push is enabled for this favourite.

BusinessLine.description: This field contains BusinessLine information when we can extract it out of search category
x-enum-descriptions: None specified.
All
Marketplace
